<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1925-08-30T00:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1925-08-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="596" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d596">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/6568: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1925-08-30T13:00:00+08:00"><hi rend="italic">August 30,
                                        1925—1 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received August 30—3:55
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>363. Consul at Amoy reports today situation quiet, boycott weakening.
                            Presence of United States ship <hi rend="italic">Hart</hi> no longer
                            necessary.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>